         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">n</mi>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mo class="mo">[</mo>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">R</mi>
            <mo class="mo">≥</mo>
            <mrow class="mrow">
             <mo class="mo">⟨</mo>
             <mi class="mi">R</mi>
             <mo class="mo">⟩</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mspace width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
            <mo class="mo">&amp;</mo>
            <mspace width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
            <mi class="mi">f</mi>
            <mo class="mo">≤</mo>
            <msub class="msub">
             <mi class="mi">f</mi>
             <mtext class="mtext">th</mtext>
            </msub>
           </mrow>
           <mo class="mo">]</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mo class="mo">+</mo>
          <mi class="mi">n</mi>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mo class="mo">[</mo>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">R</mi>
            <mo class="mo">≥</mo>
            <mrow class="mrow">
             <mo class="mo">⟨</mo>
             <mi class="mi">R</mi>
             <mo class="mo">⟩</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mspace width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
            <mo class="mo">&amp;</mo>
            <mspace width="0.166667em" class="mspace"/>
            <mi class="mi">f</mi>
            <mo class="mo">&gt;</mo>
            <msub class="msub">
             <mi class="mi">f</mi>
             <mtext class="mtext">th</mtext>
            </msub>
           </mrow>
           <mo class="mo">]</mo>
          </mrow>
         </mrow>
        </mfrac>
        <mo class="mo">,</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mtd>
     </mtr>
    </mtable>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(13)</label>
 </disp-formula> where 
 <italic class="italic">n</italic> denotes the number of days where the conditions are satisfied [
 <xref rid="pone.0201457.ref057" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">57</xref>]. A compromise must be found between a maximum sensitivity for high values of 
 <italic class="italic">f</italic>
 <sub class="sub">th</sub> and a minimum fraction of false predictions for low values of 
 <italic class="italic">f</italic>
 <sub class="sub">th</sub>. A common choice is to choose the value 
 <italic class="italic">f</italic>
 <sub class="sub">th</sub> which minimizes (1 − SEN)
 <sup class="sup">2</sup> + FFP
 <sup class="sup">2</sup> [
 <xref rid="pone.0201457.ref057" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">57</xref>] (see also Fig C in 
 <xref ref-type="supplementary-material" rid="pone.0201457.s001" class="xref">S1 Appendix</xref> (ROC-curve)). Under the assumption that the meaning of the 
 <italic class="italic">f</italic>-parameter does not depend on GCM and time frame, we use the derived 
 <italic class="italic">f</italic>
 <sub class="sub">th</sub> to estimate the duration of low wind periods as described in above.
</p>
